dcterms:description: Gravitational wave signals from binary black holes (BBH) used for training a conditional variational autoencoder (CVAE) to estimate posterior probability distributions.
dcterms:title: BBH signals

dcterms:description: A collection of 256 multi-detector gravitational wave test waveforms used to evaluate the performance of the CVAE against traditional Bayesian methods.
dcterms:title: 256 multi-detector GW test BBH waveforms

dcterms:description: A database containing gravitational-wave candidate events from the LIGO and Virgo collaborations, specifically from the O3 observing run.
dcterms:title: Gracedb gravitational-wave candidate event database

dcterms:creator: S. Khan
K. Chatziioannou
M. Hannam
F. Ohme
dcterms:description: A phenomenological model for the gravitational-wave signal from precessing binary black holes, incorporating two-spin effects.
dcterms:title: IMRPhenomPv2 waveform model

dcterms:description: Nine parameters related to binary black hole signals that are analyzed in the context of the study, including masses, distances, and angles.
dcterms:title: 9 parameters for BBH signals
